"You won't develop a sexual attraction to people you grow up with in your earliest years" is the gist of it.

iirc there's experimental evidence to suggest it's not quite correct, but as a rule of thumb something like it seems to feature in human psychology. There's not really a lot of scope to try and improve our understanding of whatever is at play here, for obvious ethics reasons let alone the insane financial and temporal cost for any sort of formal experiment, so we're limited to the tiny, extremely noisy source of in-situ observation.
